### 1. HEALTH CHECK
GET http://localhost:2310/api/v1/health

### 2. REGISTER - Nuovo utente
POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!",
  "username": "alice123",
  "nome": "Alice",
  "cognome": "Rossi"
}


### 3. REGISTER - Secondo utente
POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass456!",
  "username": "bob456",
  "nome": "Bob",
  "cognome": "Verdi"
}

### 4. LOGIN - Credenziali corrette (Alice)
POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

### 5. LOGIN - Password sbagliata
POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword"
}

### 6. LOGIN - Email non esistente
POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nonexistent@example.com",
  "password": "AnyPassword123!"
}

### 7. REGISTER - Email duplicata (dovrebbe fallire)
POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "DifferentPassword789!",
  "username": "alice789",
  "nome": "Alice2",
  "cognome": "Rossi2"
}

### 8. LOGIN - Alice per ottenere token
POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("auth_token", response.body.token);
    client.global.set("user_id", response.body.user.id);
    console.log("✓ Token salvato: " + response.body.token.substring(0, 20) + "...");
    console.log("✓ User ID: " + response.body.user.id);
%}

### 9. LOGIN - Bob per ottenere token (alternativo)
POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass456!"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("auth_token_bob", response.body.token);
    console.log("✓ Token Bob salvato: " + response.body.token.substring(0, 20) + "...");
%}

### 10. PROTECTED - Accedi con token (Alice)
GET http://localhost:2310/api/v1/protected
Authorization: Bearer {{ auth_token }}

### 11. PROTECTED - Accedi con token (Bob - alternativo)
GET http://localhost:2310/api/v1/protected
Authorization: Bearer {{ auth_token_bob }}

### 12. PROTECTED - Senza token (dovrebbe fallire 401)
GET http://localhost:2310/api/v1/protected

### 13. PROTECTED - Con token non valido (dovrebbe fallire 401)
GET http://localhost:2310/api/v1/protected
Authorization: Bearer invalid.token.here

### 14. REGISTER - Password troppo corta (validation error)
POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "",
  "password": "",
  "username": "",
  "nome": "",
  "cognome": ""
}
### 15. VERIFICA - Verifica email Alice
POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/verifica-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com"
}


### NOTE SUI TEST:
###
### • Per test manuali con curl:
###   1. Register: curl -X POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/register -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"email":"user@test.com","password":"SecurePass123!","nome":"Nome","cognome":"Cognome"}'
###   2. Login: curl -X POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/login -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"email":"user@test.com","password":"SecurePass123!"}' | jq
###   3. Estrai token: TOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST http://localhost:2310/api/v1/auth/login -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"email":"user@test.com","password":"SecurePass123!"}' | jq -r '.token')
###   4. Usa token: curl -H "Authorization: Bearer ${TOKEN}" http://localhost:2310/api/v1/protected
###
### • VARIABILI SALVATE AUTOMATICAMENTE:
###   - auth_token: token JWT di Alice (disponibile per i test successivi)
###   - user_id: ID utente Alice
###   - auth_token_bob: token JWT di Bob
###   Usale nei test futuri con {{ auth_token }} o {{ user_id }}
